commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented Student class and associated classes. Implemented Planner class and associated classes. Implemented Programme and GraduationRequirements class and associated classes.
Updated ModuleDataImporter to use NUSMods API v2
#37 Implemented Planner, Module, ModuleDataImport Removed StudentAddCommand to be better implemented by Vincent.
Implement `remark` command Remarks can now be added with the `remark [index] r/[remark]` command. However, remarks are not saved between sessions.
Fix checkstyle errors Fixes checkstyleMain errors to allow Travis CI build to pass.

commitResults.messageBody:
Enrollment and TimeTable have been added.

SemesterYear and StudentSemester now have `hashCode` and `equals` methods.

`User` has been provisionally added, but will be removed in a future
commit.

Stubs have been added for the `declare` command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `declare major` and stubs for `module` commands
commitResults.messageBody:
`declare major` has been implemented together with serialization of the
major.

Stubs for `module add`, `module remove` and `module list` have been
added. The module codes are syntatically validated to be alphanumeric, but are not
yet validated for existence in module database.

Serialization is changed slightly with addition of `activeStudent`
field.

Some reorganization of code is done, but this is restricted to reduce merge
conflicts with other PRs.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `module add, remove, list` and module code serialization
commitResults.messageBody:
`module add`, `module remove` and `module list` have been implemented.

Serialization of the module code list has also been implemented.

Tentatively, these commands save module codes to a separate field in
`planner.json`. Amendments will be made in future commits to save module
`Enrollment`s in `TimeTable`s stored by `Student`s in later commits.
This is partly to alleviate the problem of merge conflicts from other
PRs.

`student add`, `student remove` and `student active` are now
implemented.

Currently, there must be at least one student in the student list.
Therefore, removing a student is forbidden if there is only one student.

Students can be added with their name and major:
`student add n/Alice major/CS`. Duplicate students are forbidden.

A student can be set as the active student with
`student active [INDEX]`, where `INDEX` is a one-based index.

Currently, students only store their name and major. This will be
changed in future commits which will store timetables and matriculation
requirements in `Student`.

A valid sample planner is now used if the `planner.json` file cannot be
loaded or is invalid. This keeps the planner state valid.

`student list` which shows the list of students added is now implemented.
